defs.name: Simulation
defs.docs:
In the original python implementation, this was a `sim` object.
 Here, we rename it SpatialGrid, since it is just a spatial grid
 (and its fourier transform) with several fields

defs.name: FftObject
defs.docs:
This struct is intended to be initialized at the
 beginning of a simulation. It holds the forward
 and inverse fft objects that process FFTs.
